{
  "page": "Cape Wrath",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Stormlands.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"The stormlands and the location of the Cape Wrath\"><img alt=\"The stormlands and the location of the Cape Wrath\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/The_Stormlands.png/400px-The_Stormlands.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/The_Stormlands.png/600px-The_Stormlands.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/The_Stormlands.png/800px-The_Stormlands.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 66.7%; left: 70.8%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -6px; top: -6px; width: 12px; font-size: 12px;\"><img alt=\"The stormlands and the location of the Cape Wrath\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/12px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Cape Wrath\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/18px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/24px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size: 90%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; top:-2.65em; left:-3em; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\"><b>Cape Wrath</b></span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\">The <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> and the location of Cape Wrath\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><table>\n\n<tbody><tr><td></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Cape Wrath</b>, or the <b>Cape of Wrath</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is a large peninsula of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> that juts out into the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>, bordered to the north by <a href=\"/index.php/Shipbreaker_Bay\" title=\"Shipbreaker Bay\">Shipbreaker Bay</a>, to the east by <a href=\"/index.php/Estermont\" title=\"Estermont\">Estermont</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>, and to the south by the <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_of_Dorne\" title=\"Sea of Dorne\">Sea of Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiaf_cape_wrath.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiaf_cape_wrath.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Geography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Geography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Geography\">Geography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Geography\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lino_Drieghe_Cape_Wrath.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a0/Lino_Drieghe_Cape_Wrath.JPG/300px-Lino_Drieghe_Cape_Wrath.JPG\" width=\"300\" height=\"195\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a0/Lino_Drieghe_Cape_Wrath.JPG/450px-Lino_Drieghe_Cape_Wrath.JPG 1.5x, /images/a/a0/Lino_Drieghe_Cape_Wrath.JPG 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lino_Drieghe_Cape_Wrath.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A ship in a storm at Cape Wrath, by Lino Drieghe © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>Cape Wrath is dominated by the <a href=\"/index.php/Rainwood\" title=\"Rainwood\">rainwood</a>, which includes <a href=\"/index.php/Mistwood\" title=\"Mistwood\">Mistwood</a> in the south of the forest and <a href=\"/index.php/Rain_House\" title=\"Rain House\">Rain House</a> at its eastern edge. South of the forest is a broad plain. The southern coast of the peninsula is full of stone watchtowers raised to warn of <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornish</a> raiders from the sea. Numerous villages were built around these now-ruined towers, with a few eventually growing into towns.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ar2_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ar2-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> One of these is the prosperous <a href=\"/index.php/Weeping_Town\" title=\"Weeping Town\">Weeping Town</a>, where much of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>' trade passes through.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The western edge of the peninsula is mountainous and includes <a href=\"/index.php/Stonehelm\" title=\"Stonehelm\">Stonehelm</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Watch\" title=\"Red Watch\">Red Watch</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Crow%27s_Nest\" title=\"Crow&#39;s Nest\">Crow's Nest</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Griffin%27s_Roost\" title=\"Griffin&#39;s Roost\">Griffin's Roost</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafwesteros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafwesteros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Houses <a href=\"/index.php/House_Brownhill_(stormlands)\" title=\"House Brownhill (stormlands)\">Brownhill</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Seaworth\" title=\"House Seaworth\">Seaworth</a> have also held lands on Cape Wrath.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racokprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racokprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> There are a myriad of small isles<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> off the southern coast of the peninsula in the <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_of_Dorne\" title=\"Sea of Dorne\">Sea of Dorne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafwesteros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafwesteros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Although it is rainy, Cape Wrath is fertile enough.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Storms which begin in the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Sea\" title=\"Summer Sea\">Summer Sea</a> slam into Cape Wrath as they head north.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ar2_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ar2-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marya_Seaworth.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/30/Marya_Seaworth.jpg/300px-Marya_Seaworth.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"196\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/3/30/Marya_Seaworth.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marya_Seaworth.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Marya_Seaworth\" title=\"Marya Seaworth\">Marya Seaworth</a> by Yulia Startsev © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The woods of Cape Wrath were inhabited in antiquity by the <a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_coming_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_the_coming_of_the_first_men.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> but the cape came to be controlled by the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>.\n</p><p>A <a href=\"/index.php/Woods_witch\" title=\"Woods witch\">woods witch</a> called the <a href=\"/index.php/Green_Queen\" title=\"Green Queen\">Green Queen</a> rebelled against the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm King</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Durwald_I_Durrandon\" title=\"Durwald I Durrandon\">Durwald I Durrandon</a>, controlling the <a href=\"/index.php/Rainwood\" title=\"Rainwood\">rainwood</a> for a generation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> During the <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_the_Andals\" title=\"Coming of the Andals\">coming of the Andals</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> would have conquered all of Cape Wrath from the First Men if not for their own disunity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>With King <a href=\"/index.php/Argilac_Durrandon\" title=\"Argilac Durrandon\">Argilac Durrandon</a> preoccupied with the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryens</a>, pirates from the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a> raided the cape during <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_8_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">8&#160;AC</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Dornish_War\" title=\"First Dornish War\">First Dornish War</a>, a pirate king from the Stepstones transported <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a> across the <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_of_Dorne\" title=\"Sea of Dorne\">Sea of Dorne</a> to Cape Wrath. The raiders attacked six towns and villages and set fires in the rainwood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During her search for the missing <a href=\"/index.php/Aerea_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerea Targaryen\">Aerea Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a> and her dragon, <a href=\"/index.php/Dreamfyre\" title=\"Dreamfyre\">Dreamfyre</a>, were seen flying over Cape Wrath.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Morion_Martell\" title=\"Morion Martell\">Morion Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a>, vowed to burn a hundred towns and a hundred castles on Cape Wrath during the ill-fated <a href=\"/index.php/Fourth_Dornish_War\" title=\"Fourth Dornish War\">Fourth Dornish War</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/83_AC\" title=\"83 AC\">83&#160;AC</a>, although the peninsula does not have a third that number of such settlements. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Boremund_Baratheon\" title=\"Boremund Baratheon\">Boremund Baratheon</a> readied a host to defend Cape Wrath against the invaders. <a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a> burned Morion's ships as they crossed the sea, however, and Dornish corpses washed ashore for months.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Weeping_Town\" title=\"Weeping Town\">Weeping Town</a> is so named because it is where the body of King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron I Targaryen\">Daeron I Targaryen</a> was first brought after his death in Dorne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End\">siege of Storm's End</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> granted <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> a small keep and choice lands on Cape Wrath,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> including woods in which he can hunt <a href=\"/index.php/Red_deer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Red deer\">red deer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> sends <a href=\"/index.php/Dale_Seaworth\" title=\"Dale Seaworth\">Dale Seaworth</a> to sail <i><a href=\"/index.php/Wraith\" title=\"Wraith\">Wraith</a></i> along Cape Wrath, the <a href=\"/index.php/Broken_Arm\" title=\"Broken Arm\">Broken Arm</a>, the coast of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Arbor\" title=\"Arbor\">Arbor</a>, informing the populace of Stannis's claim to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/82/Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg/300px-Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/82/Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg/450px-Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/82/Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg/600px-Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mariana_Vieira_Aegon%27s_FavorIII.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rolly_Duckfield\" title=\"Rolly Duckfield\">Rolly Duckfield</a> kneels before Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, by Mariana Vieira © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>Cape Wrath is invaded during the <a href=\"/index.php/Landing_of_the_Golden_Company\" title=\"Landing of the Golden Company\">landing of the Golden Company</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a>. While a quarter of <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">the sellswords'</a> available strength is taking <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_Griffin%27s_Roost\" title=\"Taking of Griffin&#39;s Roost\">Griffin's Roost</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tristan_Rivers\" title=\"Tristan Rivers\">Tristan Rivers</a> sets off simultaneously for the seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Morrigen\" title=\"House Morrigen\">House Morrigen</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_Crow%27s_Nest\" title=\"Taking of Crow&#39;s Nest\">Crow's Nest</a>, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Laswell_Peake\" title=\"Laswell Peake\">Laswell Peake</a> for <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_Rain_House\" title=\"Taking of Rain House\">Rain House</a>, the stronghold of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Wylde\" title=\"House Wylde\">House Wylde</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Harry_Strickland\" title=\"Harry Strickland\">Harry Strickland</a> argues that if Tristan and Laswell are successful the Golden Company will control a better part of Cape Wrath.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup> The castles fall quickly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafcrow.27s_nest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_21-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafcrow.27s_nest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafrain_house.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_22-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafrain_house.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-22\">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Marya_Seaworth\" title=\"Marya Seaworth\">Marya</a> was mistress of a small keep on Cape Wrath, with servants who called her m'lady, and Davos could hunt red <a href=\"/index.php/Deer\" title=\"Deer\">deer</a> in his own woods. All this he had of <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>, for the price of a few finger joints.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok10.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Only a few years ago, he would never have dared attempt a landing on Cape Wrath; the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">storm lords</a> were too fiercely loyal to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon\" title=\"House Baratheon\">House Baratheon</a> and to King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>. But with both Robert and his brother <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly</a> slain, everything was changed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The location may have been named in reference to <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cape_Wrath\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Cape Wrath\">Cape Wrath</a>, a cape in the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scottish_Highlands\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Scottish Highlands\">Scottish Highlands</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Cape_Wrath&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight\" title=\"The Hedge Knight\">The Hedge Knight</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiaf_cape_wrath.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiaf_cape_wrath.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>,  Cape Wrath.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Map_of_the_South\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Map of the South\">Map of the South</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ar2-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ar2_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ar2_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_II_(The_Winds_of_Winter)\" title=\"Arianne II (The Winds of Winter)\">Arianne II</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">5.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\">5.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\">5.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Stormlands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Map_of_the_South_(A_Dance_with_Dragons)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Map of the South (A Dance with Dragons)\">Map of the South</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"